// video 2
In this (second) video I show you how to create lots of objects quickly (with arrays), and how to detect collisions between those objects (collision detection). This is coded in javaScript, using the p5 library (see links below for help with p5!).

The code used in this tutorial: http://codepen.io/RedHenDev/pen/VbjbRp

Links to other videos in this series: 
